    <section id="main">
      <h1>Cadmium Content Types</h1>
      <p>Cadmium provides content type mappings for hundreds of common file extensions.  If these mappings do not cover the content for your application, you can add to or override these mappings with the /META-INF/mime.json file.</p>
      <h2>Custom Content Types</h2>
      <p>The /META-INF/mime.json file provides custom type mappings for the currently deployed content.  This is an example file that maps both the .foo and .bar extensions to text/html:</p>
      <pre class="snippet">
[
  {
    "extension":"foo",
    "contentType":"text/html"
  },
  {
    "extension":"bar",
    "contentType":"text/html"
  }
]
      </pre>
    </section>
